    <h1>Web Sketchpad Accessibility</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-Overview"><span style=3D"color:=
 rgb(0,0,0);">Overview</span></h2>
<p>Accessibility of MHE content is company-wide priority, endorsed by the b=
usiness. Web Sketchpad content is currently not highly accessible. We propo=
se to address this, principally by:</p>
<ul>
<li>Supporting authorship of keyboard accessible Web Sketches (<a class=3D"=
external-link" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/#keyboard-operation" re=
l=3D"nofollow">WCAG20 2.1</a>).</li>
<li>Investigating, and as feasible implementing, screen-reader support (<a =
class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/#ensure-compat=
" rel=3D"nofollow">WCAG20 4.1</a>).</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>See <a href=3D"/display/KEY/Web+Sketchpad+Accessibility+Effort+Estimatio=
n">Web Sketchpad Accessibility Effort Estimation</a> for work estimates and=
 more detailed scoping.</p>
<h1 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-AreasforImprovement">Areas for Improvem=
ent</h1>
<p>There are three main areas where we can improve accessibility for Web Sk=
etches.</p>
<h2 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-KeyboardAccessibility">Keyboard Accessi=
bility</h2>
<h3 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-ObjectFocus">Object Focus</h3>
<p>We can support a notion of object "focus" in the web sketch, where you c=
an tab/shift-tab between objects. This would put some focus UI around the o=
bject, and enable the enter key to activate.</p>
<ul>
<li>Buttons. Enter presses the button.</li>
<li>Numeric Input Parameters. Enter brings up the number pad.</li>
<li>Calculations/Functions. Enter brings up the calculator.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-KeyboardAccessibleUI">Keyboard Accessib=
le UI</h3>
<p>Additional (and more conventional HTML accessibility) should be provided=
 for:</p>
<ul>
<li>The numeric entry pad.</li>
<li>The calculator.</li>
<li>The tool palette.</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>We can support keyboard shortcut authorship.</p>
<ul>
<li>Authors can specific a character in a button label as the shortcut (via=
 the '&amp;' prefix).</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-GeometricObjectKeyboardAccessibility">G=
eometric Object Keyboard Accessibility</h3>
<p>Keyboard accessibility for more general geometric objects can be support=
ed by:</p>
<ul>
<li>Designating keyboard shortcuts in the label of the object (via the '&am=
p;') prefix. The object then would be focusable, and participate in the tab=
 order.</li>
<li>A focused geometric object would support the arrow keys for dragging.</=
li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-ScreenReaderSupport">Screen Reader Supp=
ort</h2>
<p>Technical options for screen reader support are not yet clear. The curre=
nt plan is therefore to spike various possibilities, and formulate actionab=
le plans for screen reader support.</p>
<ul>
<li>Can we support screen readers for web sketchpad buttons, parameters, fo=
rmulas, or object labels? This would augment keyboard accessibility for the=
se objects.</li>
<li>Can we support screen readers for text components?
<ul>
<li>Can we support selection in text components, and link that to the DLE w=
idget selection -&gt; speech API?</li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-SmallerFeatures">Smaller Features</h2>
<p>These are miscellaneous features generally increasing usability, and the=
refore accessibility. We will prioritize them, and implement them (or not) =
according to priority and resource availability.</p>
<h3 id=3D"WebSketchpadAccessibility-MobileZoomSupport">Mobile Zoom Support<=
/h3>
<ul>
<li>Support for pinch-zoom would make mobile access more accessible. This w=
ould require changing the current sketch content scrolling API, as supporti=
ng dragging in whitespace to scroll interferes with the pinch-zoom gesture.=
</li>
<li>Other features and bug fixes as identified in the WSP Accessibility Epi=
c.</li>
</ul>
